text: Baker Street is an area of Orsett in the unitary authority of Thurrock. It is in the ceremonial county of Essex, England. == Description == ReaneyPH Reaney, The Place-Names of Essex (CUP, 1969) suggests the name is derived from William Bakere de Luggestreet. It is known locally because of the surviving windmill. The windmill is said to have been built in the 17th century and ceased working in 1911. It is now a private house.center ==Notes== Category:Hamlets in Essex Category:Thurrock
title: Baker Street, Essex
